Events.Text: Say hallo to the AI Assistant. [instruction 1 of 6]
Hello
Hello, how can I help you?
Hello, how can I help?
I'd like to schedule a viewing of an apartment at the One on Center Apartments, please.
You suddenly remember that you have a job interview on Wednesday at 10 pm. [instruction 2 of 6]
Can I have your name please?
Could you give me your name, please?
John.
Ask something about the apartment, or engage in smalltalk, or make a joke. [instruction 3 of 6]
What day would you like to schedule the viewing for
What day would you like to make the booking for?
Wednesday please, and are there multiple units available to view?

You cannot remember if you had payed the application fee. Find a way to make an appointment anyway. If no date is available, change date and/or time until something works. If you already got the appointment, engage in smalltalk. [instruction 4 of 6]
What time of day would you like? I will check to see if there are multiple units available to view.
I can check what units are available to view, what time would you like to schedule the viewing for?
Anytime on Wednesday is fine. I have a late interview that night at 10 pm.
Once you've scheduled the viewing, say something about your job interview. [instruction 5 of 6]
Have you paid the application fee yet?
Have you already paid the application fee for the apartment?
I can't remember, I apologize.
When you are done with all the instructions, bring the conversation to a natural close.  [instruction 6 of 6]
I have 12 pm available on Wednesday, would you like me to book it?
I can book a viewing for Wednesday at 12 pm if you would like.
That would be great. I really hope it works out because the job I am interviewing for is close to this location.
I will book the reservation now.
